5. What are the prerequisite of upgradation ?
=> i). You have to enough space on your file system 
   ii). Linux version must be 7.9
   iii). If ASM running then it has to be 19c version.

*** Suppose our ASM is running on 12c, DB is running 12c and our OS version is 7.5. now client ask to upgrade it to 19c. Now what to do ??

==>  First, OS team upgrade it to 7.9 which is required version.
	Secondly, We've to upgrade ASM to 19c first before DB. Because, ASM version always >= DB version.
	if our ASM version is 12c then our DB version has to be 12c or 11g or 10g not more than 12c version. *



6. Query running / application slowness how to resolved it and as a DBA what is your approach ?

=> i. Check the database status. If DB is up and running or not.
   ii. Check our Session is reaching beyond threshold or not. means, if our session threshold is set and active session is more than that then transaction will be interrupt.
   iii. Check listners status
   iv. Check FRA is fully filled. Because all transactions will go to FRA. 



